CREDIT  CARD  
APPROVAL  PREDICTION 
Abstract : 
The Credit Card Approval Prediction System is a web
based application developed to automate the credit 
card approval process using Machine Learning and rule
based underwriting. The system analyzes applicant 
information such as age, annual income, employment 
experience, CIBIL score, debt, and previous credit 
history to determine whether a credit card application 
should be approved or rejected. By combining a trained 
Machine Learning model with predefined banking rules, 
the application provides accurate, consistent, and 
transparent decision-making while reducing manual 
effort and processing time. 
The application is built using Python, Flask, HTML, CSS, 
and JavaScript, with Scikit-learn, XGBoost, Pandas, and 
NumPy used for data preprocessing, model training, 
and prediction. It includes separate interfaces for 
customers, analysts, and compliance officers, enabling 
users to submit applications, review prediction results, 
and verify compliance with banking policies. The trained 
model is stored using Joblib for efficient and reusable 
predictions. 
Overall, the Credit Card Approval Prediction System 
demonstrates the practical application of Machine 
Learning in the banking and financial sector by 
improving the efficiency, accuracy, and reliability of 
credit card approval decisions. It serves as a scalable 
and user-friendly solution suitable for academic projects 
and real-world financial applications. 
Problem  Statement: 
The manual credit card approval process is time
consuming, inconsistent, and prone to human error, 
as it requires the evaluation of multiple applicant 
factors such as income, credit score, employment 
history, debt, and previous credit records. These 
challenges can result in delayed decisions and 
inaccurate approvals or rejections. This project 
addresses the problem by developing a Credit Card 
Approval Prediction System that uses Machine 
Learning and rule-based underwriting to automate 
the evaluation process, improve prediction accuracy, 
reduce processing time, and support reliable, 
transparent, and efficient credit card approval 
decisions. 
