Tech  Stack : 
The Credit Card Approval Prediction System is 
developed using a combination of web development 
technologies and Machine Learning tools to ensure 
efficient, accurate, and user-friendly credit card 
approval prediction. 
Python is used as the primary programming language 
for implementing the application's backend logic, data 
processing, and Machine Learning model. It provides a 
simple and powerful environment for developing 
intelligent applications. 
The Flask framework is used to build the web 
application. It handles user requests, connects the 
frontend with the backend, processes application data, 
and displays the prediction results through a web 
interface. 
For Machine Learning, Scikit-learn is used to preprocess 
the dataset, train the prediction model, and evaluate its 
performance. The XGBoost algorithm is implemented to 
improve the accuracy and reliability of credit card 
approval predictions. 
Pandas is used for loading, cleaning, and manipulating 
the dataset, while NumPy supports numerical 
computations and efficient handling of data arrays. 
The trained Machine Learning model is saved and 
loaded using Joblib, allowing the application to make 
predictions without retraining the model every time the 
application starts. 
The user interface is developed using HTML and CSS. 
HTML is used to design the structure of the web pages, 
while CSS enhances the appearance and provides a 
responsive and user-friendly layout. Jinja2, Flask's 
templating engine, is used to dynamically render web 
pages with prediction results. 
The project uses a CSV dataset containing applicant 
information for training and testing the Machine 
Learning model. 
The application can be developed and tested using 
Google Colab for model training and Visual Studio Code 
(VS Code) for web application development. The source 
code can be managed using Git and GitHub, enabling 
version control and easy collaboration. 
Overall, this technology stack provides a robust, 
scalable, and efficient platform for developing a web
based Credit Card Approval Prediction System that 
delivers fast and accurate approval decisions. 
Installation Steps : 
1. Clone the Repository & Navigate to the Directory 
cd "credit card approval" 
• 
2. Create and Activate a Virtual Environment 
On Windows: 
python -m venv venv 
.\venv\Scripts\activate 
On macOS/Linux: 
python3 -m venv venv 
source venv/bin/activate 
3. Install Dependencies 
pip install -r requirements.txt 
4. Train/Verify the ML Model (Optional) If you need to 
regenerate the best_model.joblib binary file from the 
raw dataset: 
python ml_pipeline.py 
5. Run the Automated Tests Ensure the underwriting 
engine logic is functioning perfectly before starting the 
server: 
pytest test_underwriting.py 
6. Start the Web Server 
python app.py 
The application will be accessible at [http://127.0 
.0.1:5000/](http://127.0.0.1:5000/) in your web 
browser. 
